        public void push(T item)
          throws StackFullException
        Adds an item to the stack. Searches from the end of the array to the beginning for the first empty (null) slot.
        Throws:
        StackFullException

      • pop

        public T pop()
      throws StackEmptyException
        Removes and returns the top element of the stack. In this implementation, the "top" is the first non-null element found from index 0.
        Throws:
        StackEmptyException
